h1(#wxtoolbartool). Wx::ToolBarTool

A ToolBarTool contains information about an item added to a
"ToolBar":toolbar.thml. It is returned by methods such as
"ToolBar#add_tool":toolbar.html#ToolBar_addtool. It can be used to find
out the "ID":#ToolBarTool_getid of the newly added button or control.

Note that its methods are read-only; to actually change the state of an
item within a toolbar, make use of methods in "ToolBar":toolbar.html
such as "enable_tool":toolbar.html#ToolBar_enabletool (to disable and
enable a button), "toggle_tool":toolbar.html#ToolBar_toggletool (to
change the state of a toggle button) and
"set_tool_normal_bitmap":toolbar.html#ToolBar_settoolnormalbitmap (to
change the bitmap image used for a button).

This class should not be instantiated directly.

